innoextract
------------------------------------------
Inno Setup is a tool to create installers for Microsoft Windows applications.
innoextract allows to extract such installers under non-windows systems
without running the actual installer using Wine. innoextract currently
supports installers created by Inno Setup 1.2.10 to 6.0.5.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libboost_filesystem1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_iostreams1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_program_options1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_system1.66-1.66.0-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libiconv2-1.19-2
  liblzma5-5.8.3-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  liblzma-devel-5.8.3-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://constexpr.org/innoextract/

Canonical download:
  https://constexpr.org/innoextract/files/innoextract-1.9.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack innoextract-1.9-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./innoextract-1.9-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/innoextract-1.9-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/innoextract-1.9-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(innoextract)
  /usr/bin/innoextract.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/innoextract.README
  /usr/share/doc/innoextract/CHANGELOG
  /usr/share/doc/innoextract/CONTRIBUTING.md
  /usr/share/doc/innoextract/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/innoextract/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/innoextract/VERSION
  /usr/share/man/man1/innoextract.1.gz

